description:
The conversion of the Priory into 12 private residential
units  and the erection of a five storey block of 18
flats and nine terrace houses to be used as sheltered
accommodation with associated common rooms and a wardens
flat with seventeen associated car parking spaces as
shown on drawing nos. 6200/1G  2C  3c  4C  5C  6C  7C
8C  9D. revised on 25.10.93.
decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - Notwithstanding the provisions of Article 3 of the Town and
    Country Planning General Development Order 1988 (as
    amended) or any Order revoking and re-enacting that Order,
    no development within Part 1 (Classes A to H) and Part 2
    (Classes A to C) of Schedule 2 of that Order shall be
    carried out without the grant of planning permission having
    first been obtained from the Council.

Condition : 2 - No development shall take place until a revised layout for
    all unbuilt, open areas within the site, showing road areas,
    parking spaces and hard and soft landscaping has been
    submitted to and approved by the Council.

Condition : 3 - The whole of the car parking accommodation shown in
    drawings to be approved pursuant to Condition 02 shall be
    provided and retained permanently for the parking of
    behicles of the occupiers and users of the remainder of the
    building.

Condition : 4 - The Priory Gardens shall be permanently retained for the
    use of residents of the development hereby permitted, and
    for events and functions organised in association with St.
    Dominic's Church.

Condition : 5 - The residential dwellings shown in the terrace houses and
    end block hereby approved shall be used only for sheltered
    housing for the elderly and for no other purpose.

Condition : 6 - Full details of refuse collection and storage shall be
    submitted to the Council as Local Planning Authority for
    approval before work commences on site.

Condition : 7 - Full details of boundary treatment delineating both the
    curtilage of the site and individual plots within the site
    shallbe submitted to the Council as Local Planning
    Authority for approval before any work starts on site.

Condition : 8 - No developments shall take place until full details of hard
    and soft landscaping (including details of road materials)
    and means of enclosure of all unbuilt, open areas have been
    submitted to and approved by the Council as Local Planning
    Authority.

Condition : 9 - All hard and soft landscaping works shall be carried out to
    the end of the following planting season, with others of
    similar size and species, unless the Council gives written
    consent to any variation.
    a reasonable standard in accordance with the approved
    landscape details, prior to the occupation for the
    permitted use of the development or any phase of the
    development, whichever is the sooner. Any trees or areas of
    planting which, within a period of 5 years from the
    completion of the development die, are removed, or become
    seriously damaged or diseased, shall be replaced as soon as
    is reasonably possible and, in any case, by not later than

Condition : 10 - Full details of the glazing and window design of gable
    windows in the Priory shall be submitted to and approved by
    the Council before any works commence on site.

Condition : 11 - The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in
    strict accordance with the drawings hereby approved and
    with the approvals given pursuant to conditions 05, 06, 07,
    08 and 09 above.

Condition : 12 - To safeguard the visual amenities of the area and to
    prevent over-development of the site by controlling
    proposed extensions and alterations.

Condition : 13 - In order to ensure that the external areas will be
    satisfactory.

Condition : 14 - To ensure the permanent retention of the accommodation for
    parking purposes and to ensure that the use of the building
    does not add to traffic congestion.

Condition : 15 - To safeguard the amenities of the adjoining premises and
    the area generally.

Condition : 16 - To ensure that the accommodation is used in accordance with
    the intentions of the proposed scheme and is not used for
    unauthorised purposes.

Condition : 17 - - 08 In order that the Council may give consideration to
    the details of the proposed development.

Condition : 18 - To ensure that the landscaping is carried out within a
    reasonable period and to maintain a satisfactory standard
    of visual amenity in the scheme.
Condition : 19 - To protect the amenities of other premises.

Condition : 20 - To safeguard the appearance of the premises and the
    character of the immediate area.
